  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency intervention on sanitation in IDP off camp sites in Tikrit, Salah Al Din Governorate</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Terre des hommes (Tdh) has been involved in Iraq since November 2014 supporting Internally Displaced People (IDP) through emergency aid. Tdh has been operating in Tikrit since June 2016, where it has been implementing Wash, Child protection, Education and CCCM.

Water supply and sanitation in Tikrit is characterized by poor water and service quality. The last fighting between Iraqi Armed Forced/Shiite militia and ISIS armed group, has destroyed Tikrit&apos;s water resources management system. Thus, Tikrit water management are unable to provide safe water drinking supply and all the IDPs met in the IDPs site Complex use unsafe drinking water. 

The needs about drainage in complex informal IDPs camps are obvious. Unfinished buildings are not connected to any sewage system and households are flushing their waste water into the street . By consequence, they are faced with significant incidence of diarrhea cases, and are clearly at risks of waterborne diseases (cholera included). Also the existing sanitation blocks in the site are connected to cesspool witch will be full in few months. 
The project submitted to the pooled fund that will take place between 1st of June 2017 and 30th of November 2017 will consist in sustaining sanitation systems/services by connecting unfinished 71 buildings to cesspools by sewage system. Tdh will also desludge a part of existing cesspool of public sanitation blocks for 8664 displaced people.
Implementing this project will ensure to avoid overflowing of faeces in the camp and will eradicate pools of stagnant waste water around each building witch represent a serious vector for disease. Hygiene practices will also be improved by hygiene promotion activities.</narrative>
  </description>
